1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
 - Good morning everyone.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:08,340
 And we will continue our series on the Psalms in the Bible.

3
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:10,600
 And as I told you before,

4
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:14,600
 many of the Psalms were originally prayers

5
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:16,860
 spoken by the people of God.

6
00:00:16,860 --> 00:00:19,520
 But some of the Psalms in the book of Psalms

7
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,000
 are written for the purpose of teaching us something.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,360
 So teaching us how to relate to God,

9
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:28,480
 teaching us how to see ourselves and see the world.

10
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:32,400
 (speaking in foreign language)

11
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:46,360
 Now we call these kinds of Psalms, wisdom Psalms.

12
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:48,800
 You may have heard it the very first time today,

13
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,540
 but we can call them wisdom Psalms

14
00:00:51,540 --> 00:00:56,540
 because these wisdom Psalms are meant to teach us something,

15
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:59,240
 to teach us wisdom, make us wiser

16
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:02,660
 and help us better relate to God.

17
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:06,580
 (speaking in foreign language)

18
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:17,140
 And let's read this, Psalm 1, okay?

19
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:19,120
 So Psalm 1 has six verses.

20
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,000
 Let's read that verse by verse.

21
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,880
 Let me begin with English.

22
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,760
 Psalm 1, verse 1.

23
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,180
 "Thus is the man who does not walk

24
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:29,500
 in the counsel of the wicked,

25
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,860
 or stand in the way of sinners,

26
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:35,740
 or sit in the seat of mockers."

27
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:39,660
 (speaking in foreign language)

28
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:47,320
 But his delight is in the law of the Lord,

29
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,880
 and on his law he meditates day and night.

30
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:54,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

31
00:01:54,800 --> 00:02:01,780
 And verse 3, "He is like a tree planted by streams of water,

32
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:04,620
 which yields its fruit in season,

33
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:06,720
 and whose leaf does not wither.

34
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:09,100
 Whatever he does prospers."

35
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:13,020
 (speaking in foreign language)

36
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:21,780
 Not so the wicked, they are like a shaft,

37
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:25,020
 and that the wind blows away.

38
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:29,700
 (speaking in foreign language)

39
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,260
 And verse 5, "Therefore the wicked

40
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:32,940
 will not stand in judgment,

41
00:02:32,940 --> 00:02:36,140
 nor sinners in the assembly of the righteous."

42
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:40,060
 (speaking in foreign language)

43
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:45,100
 And verse 6, "For the Lord watches over

44
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,620
 the way of the righteous,

45
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:49,100
 but the way of the wicked will perish."

46
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:53,020
 (speaking in foreign language)

47
00:02:53,020 --> 00:02:57,820
 Now Psalm 1 is the first Psalm in the book of Sardar,

48
00:02:57,820 --> 00:03:01,300
 and it is like a gate to the temple of God.

49
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:03,060
 So before you enter the temple of God,

50
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:05,200
 there was a gate that you have to go through,

51
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,060
 and you walk into the presence of God,

52
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:08,900
 the most holy place.

53
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:11,980
 So Psalm 1 is like the gate of the temple.

54
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:15,900
 (speaking in foreign language)

55
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:19,240
 So the first word of Psalm 1 verse 1

56
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,240
 is the word we translate blessed.

57
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:25,460
 And in the Old Testament, there were two words of blessing.

58
00:03:25,460 --> 00:03:30,460
 And you have to note that, okay?

59
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:34,620
 (speaking in foreign language)

60
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:37,420
 Now the first word I give you is Barak.

61
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:40,900
 And that is the word we use to describe

62
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,420
 the blessing of God.

63
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:45,420
 (speaking in foreign language)

64
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:50,420
 To mean like we bless you because we wanna grant you

65
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:53,820
 or give you the power of life.

66
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:56,660
 You know, being blessed, being fruitful.

67
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:59,380
 You know, you recall Genesis 1,

68
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:02,460
 when God created the world, He blessed humankind.

69
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:05,060
 He blessed the world, be fruitful and multiply.

70
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:07,060
 And that is the word Barak.

71
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:10,980
 (speaking in foreign language)

72
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:13,620
 Okay, so learn this word, Barak, okay?

73
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:15,180
 Say it with me, okay?

74
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:16,020
 (speaking in foreign language)

75
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:16,860
 Barak, okay?

76
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:20,060
 But that is not the word in Psalm 1, 1, okay?

77
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,380
 That is interesting.

78
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:24,980
 That's the second Hebrew word we translate blessed

79
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:27,380
 or blessing, and that is ashare.

80
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:32,380
 We also translate it as blessed most of the time.

81
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:36,500
 (speaking in foreign language)

82
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,900
 That's blessed most of the time.

83
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:42,820
 (speaking in foreign language)

84
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:49,780
 So it doesn't mean like give you life or empower you.

85
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:54,420
 It gives you hope and it focuses on something in the future

86
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:59,420
 that you will receive future reward and final blessing.

87
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:04,500
 So this means a blessed person in Psalm 1

88
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,860
 do have difficulties now.

89
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:12,660
 (speaking in foreign language)

90
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:21,180
 And then this same word, ashare, say it with me, ashare.

91
00:05:21,180 --> 00:05:22,020
 (speaking in foreign language)

92
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:24,220
 Ashare, okay, so you learn some Hebrew word.

93
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:28,860
 The word ashare is also used in another book

94
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:33,220
 called the Book of Job, chapter five, verse 17.

95
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:36,020
 See the word being translated is also blessed.

96
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:38,660
 And the word behind it, the Hebrew word behind it

97
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:41,420
 is ashare, not barak.

98
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:44,780
 So blessed is the one whom God disciplines.

99
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:47,980
 That is Job 5, 17.

100
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:50,060
 Now, of course, when you think about discipline,

101
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:52,940
 God disciplines someone, right?

102
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:55,780
 And you call that someone blessed.

103
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:58,880
 You know, in the state of being disciplined,

104
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,300
 do you feel happy or do you feel good about it?

105
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,740
 Usually not, right?

106
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:04,860
 Usually not.

107
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:09,020
 But it's called blessed is the person whom God discipline.

108
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:12,980
 So discipline does not feel joyful at the time,

109
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:17,980
 but at the end, you will receive the benefits of discipline.

110
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:24,140
 (speaking in foreign language)

111
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:29,140
 Now, for example, if you do a physical exercise regularly,

112
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:50,700
 anyone, one of you go to the gym, you go to exercise,

113
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,900
 you go to do physical exercise.

114
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:55,540
 When you start out working out, okay,

115
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:59,260
 when you start to work out, does it feel good?

116
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:02,340
 No, it shouldn't feel good, right?

117
00:07:02,340 --> 00:07:05,260
 If you feel good when you started doing exercise,

118
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:07,220
 you're doing it wrong, okay?

119
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:10,340
 It doesn't feel good when you started to discipline yourself,

120
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:11,540
 discipline your body.

121
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:15,500
 It hurts at first, but you are still blessed

122
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:20,300
 because if you keep going, if you keep persevering,

123
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:22,940
 then you will receive the final blessing, right?

124
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:25,140
 You will receive the final reward.

125
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:29,060
 (speaking in foreign language)

126
00:07:29,060 --> 00:07:43,500
 Or another example is a student.

127
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:47,980
 You go to study and in the beginning of the semester,

128
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:51,300
 does it feel good or does it feel happy?

129
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:54,300
 Usually not, right?

130
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,460
 You feel painful as you go through the semester,

131
00:07:57,460 --> 00:08:01,380
 but you see the good result will be at the end,

132
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:04,180
 and so the blessing is not here and now,

133
00:08:04,180 --> 00:08:06,260
 it's something in the future.

134
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:10,180
 (speaking in foreign language)

135
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:14,300
 (speaking in foreign language)

136
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:25,940
 So Psalm 11 says, "Blessed is the man who does this

137
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:29,260
 "or does not do those, this things or that things."

138
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:33,500
 He's talking about the final blessing, final result.

139
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:38,060
 And Jesus used the same word in Beatitudes,

140
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:39,420
 in the book of Matthew.

141
00:08:39,420 --> 00:08:44,300
 He said, plus, he used the same word in Greek now

142
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:47,580
 because New Testament is written in Greek, not in Hebrew,

143
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:50,020
 but it's translated in Greek, makaria,

144
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:54,660
 and that is being used by Jesus in Beatitudes.

145
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:59,980
 (speaking in foreign language)

146
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:07,740
 And the same word, as share makaria.

147
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:09,700
 Okay, say makaria with me, okay?

148
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:11,300
 Makaria. - Makaria.

149
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,740
 - Makaria, okay?

150
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:15,940
 All right, so as I give you some example here,

151
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:19,540
 Jesus said, "Blessed are the poor in spirit,

152
00:09:19,540 --> 00:09:23,860
 "and blessed are those persecuted for righteousness."

153
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:28,380
 (speaking in foreign language)

154
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,820
 Now, when you're going through suffering or persecution,

155
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:31,780
 it doesn't feel good, right?

156
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,020
 The early church faced the same problem.

157
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:37,180
 They had suffering and they had persecution,

158
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:39,580
 but Jesus say, "If you belong to the kingdom,

159
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:41,340
 "the final reward will be yours,

160
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:43,700
 "and final reward will be great."

161
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:47,780
 (speaking in foreign language)

162
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:53,340
 So I think Psalm 1:1 can be translated this way,

163
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:55,540
 and that's my translation.

164
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:56,780
 It can be translated,

165
00:09:56,780 --> 00:10:01,700
 the person who will be ultimately rewarded by God

166
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:04,300
 is someone who does not walk in the counsel of wicked

167
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,460
 and this and that.

168
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:10,380
 (speaking in foreign language)

169
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:19,980
 So it's not talking about here and now

170
00:10:19,980 --> 00:10:21,740
 that you will feel happy.

171
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:23,580
 It's talking about ultimately,

172
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:28,100
 at the end of your life, you will feel blessed, okay?

173
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:31,100
 So as we go through Psalm 1,1,

174
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:34,860
 you also, the Psalm also unpacks

175
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,740
 how a blessed person will be.

176
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:41,460
 He says he does not walk and does not stand

177
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:42,980
 and does not sit.

178
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:45,420
 And you see the progression here, right?

179
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:47,780
 It's like a poem progression from walking

180
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,820
 to standing to sitting,

181
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:54,820
 and describe how the spiritual drift can happen gradually.

182
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:59,060
 To walk is being influenced by the wicked,

183
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:00,940
 by the opinions of the wicked.

184
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:04,140
 And to stand is to linger,

185
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:07,300
 to identify yourself with them.

186
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:09,980
 To sit is to settle down, right?

187
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:13,940
 To feel belong and feel comfortable with the wicked.

188
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:17,860
 (speaking in foreign language)

189
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:21,780
 (speaking in foreign language)

190
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:39,020
 And you see the movement is from motion,

191
00:11:39,020 --> 00:11:42,780
 walking to permanence, right?

192
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:47,460
 So in showing us compromises can slowly happen

193
00:11:47,460 --> 00:11:50,660
 and become a fixed way of lifestyle.

194
00:11:50,660 --> 00:11:54,580
 (speaking in foreign language)

195
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:59,220
 But the person who is blessed,

196
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:01,540
 who see the final reward,

197
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:04,380
 is someone who does not do those, right?

198
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:05,220
 Does not do those.

199
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,260
 The righteous, not the wicked,

200
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,700
 the righteous will fear God

201
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:13,380
 and may at this time disadvantage themselves.

202
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:15,220
 The righteous will disadvantage themselves

203
00:12:15,220 --> 00:12:18,180
 to advantage others.

204
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,460
 But the wicked will ignore God.

205
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:24,060
 The wicked will not see God, will not fear God.

206
00:12:24,060 --> 00:12:29,060
 And they will disadvantage others for their own advantages.

207
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:33,140
 (speaking in foreign language)

208
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:42,220
 So it says the righteous does not do those things.

209
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:45,140
 It's an invitation.

210
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:49,580
 The first Psalm of the Bible is to invite you

211
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:54,260
 to make a decision to be like the righteous

212
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:56,460
 and blessed person before God.

213
00:12:56,460 --> 00:13:00,380
 (speaking in foreign language)

214
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:03,660
 Now let's continue.

215
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:06,940
 Verse two, continue to describe this person.

216
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:09,140
 And it says the righteous person is,

217
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:13,700
 has having delight, a happy delight

218
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,260
 in the law of the Lord.

219
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:20,180
 (speaking in foreign language)

220
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:27,020
 It's talking about the inner direction of your heart, right?

221
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:31,380
 It's not something behavioral, it's not legalism.

222
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:36,380
 It's some sort of acquired taste for the righteous person.

223
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:40,460
 Okay, he acquired the taste, the delight

224
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:43,580
 in the law of God.

225
00:13:43,580 --> 00:13:46,940
 And it's kind of like acquired taste.

226
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:51,660
 It's kind of like, you like coffee or durian?

227
00:13:51,660 --> 00:13:53,380
 Something like that.

228
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:55,820
 It's not a natural taste.

229
00:13:55,820 --> 00:13:56,940
 It's acquired taste.

230
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:59,820
 I like coffee, I take coffee every single day.

231
00:13:59,820 --> 00:14:03,240
 And I didn't like it before when I was much younger.

232
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,920
 But I acquired that taste.

233
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:08,420
 Now the righteous, it's the same thing here.

234
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:11,740
 He trains himself, like a student,

235
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:16,060
 he trains himself, his mind to desire the word of God.

236
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:19,980
 (speaking in foreign language)

237
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:41,420
 And here he says he meditates day and night.

238
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:44,380
 And it does not mean emptying your mind.

239
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:47,940
 You know, I recall one of the experiences I had

240
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:50,380
 when I was a college student.

241
00:14:50,380 --> 00:14:54,900
 I took Philosophy 101, and the philosophy professor

242
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:57,820
 asked the students in the lecture hall,

243
00:14:57,820 --> 00:15:00,300
 all of us, to empty our mind.

244
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,140
 You know, he was trying to do some exercise,

245
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:05,620
 some sort of transcendental meditation.

246
00:15:05,620 --> 00:15:10,620
 So you have to empty your mind and then imagine something.

247
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:14,660
 You know, that is the secular meditation.

248
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:19,580
 (speaking in foreign language)

249
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:35,300
 And then in the Bible, biblical meditation is different.

250
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:40,100
 It means you think about it, think about the word of God.

251
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:42,820
 You study the word of God.

252
00:15:42,820 --> 00:15:44,500
 You question the word of God.

253
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:47,220
 You examine the word of God.

254
00:15:47,220 --> 00:15:51,140
 (speaking in foreign language)

255
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:58,980
 And it says day and night, it does not mean 24/7.

256
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:02,380
 It means habit, something customary.

257
00:16:02,380 --> 00:16:05,420
 You don't neglect it.

258
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:08,220
 You know, it's like your habit every day.

259
00:16:08,220 --> 00:16:12,140
 (speaking in foreign language)

260
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,980
 And then it also tells you that the object of meditation

261
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:21,740
 is Torah, or we translate the law of the Lord.

262
00:16:21,740 --> 00:16:27,780
 Torah, actually, a better translation would be instruction,

263
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:30,140
 guidance, or teaching.

264
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:34,060
 (speaking in foreign language)

265
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:43,460
 Now, the word Torah, or translated in English, law,

